#. <section class="sutta" id="ma1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "ma1:0.1"
msgid "“中阿含 1”,"
msgstr "“Middle-Length Discourses 1”,"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "ma1:0.2"
msgid "“1. 七法品”,"
msgstr "“1. The Sevens”,"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "ma1:0.3"
msgid "“1. 善法經”,"
msgstr "“1. The Good Dharma”,"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "ma1:1.1"
msgid "“我聞如是：”,"
msgstr "“I have heard thus:”,"

#. </span>
msgctxt "ma1:1.2"
msgid "“一時，佛遊舍衛國，在勝林給孤獨園。”,"
msgstr "“One time, the Buddha traveled to the kingdom of Śrāvastī and stayed at Anāthapiṇḍada Park in Jeta Grove.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:2.1"
msgid "“爾時，世尊告諸比丘：”,"
msgstr "“At that time, the Bhagavān addressed the bhikṣus:”,"

msgctxt "ma1:2.2"
msgid "“「若有比丘成就七法者，便於賢聖得歡喜樂，正趣漏盡。”,"
msgstr "“If a bhikṣu accomplishes seven things, then he will attain the happiness of the noble ones, and he will be rightly destined for the end of the contaminants.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:2.3"
msgid "“云何為七？”,"
msgstr "“What are the seven?”,"

msgctxt "ma1:2.4"
msgid "“謂比丘知法、知義、知時、知節、知己、知眾、知人勝如。”,"
msgstr "“Namely, a bhikṣu knows the Dharma, knows the meaning, knows the time, knows moderation, knows himself, knows the assembly, and knows the greater likenesses of people.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:3.1"
msgid "“「云何比丘為知法耶？”,"
msgstr "“How does a bhikṣu know the Dharma?”,"

msgctxt "ma1:3.2"
msgid "“謂比丘知正經、歌詠、記說、偈咃、因緣、撰錄、本起、此說、生處、廣解、未曾有法及說是義，”,"
msgstr "“It means a bhikṣu knows the right sūtras (discourses), songs (geya), predictions (vyākaraṇa), gāthās (verses), histories (nidāna), stories (avadāna), past births (itivṛttaka), lectures (udāna), birth places (jātaka), extensive explanations (vaipulya), unprecedented things (adbhuta-dharma), and explanations of meaning (upadeśa).”,"

msgctxt "ma1:3.3"
msgid "“是謂比丘為知法也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who knows the Dharma.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:3.4"
msgid "“若有比丘不知法者，謂不知正經、歌詠、記說、偈咃、因緣、撰錄、本起、此說、生處、廣解、未曾有法及說義，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who doesn’t know the Dharma, which is to say that he doesn’t know the right sūtras, songs, predictions, gāthās, histories, stories, past births, lectures, birth places, extensive explanations, unprecedented things, and explanations of meaning.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:3.5"
msgid "“如是比丘為不知法。”,"
msgstr "“Such a bhikṣu doesn’t know the Dharma.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:3.6"
msgid "“若有比丘善知法者，謂知正經、歌詠、記說、偈咃、因緣、撰錄、本起、此說、生處、廣解、未曾有法及說義，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who well knows the Dharma, which is to say that he knows the right sūtras, songs, predictions, gāthās, histories, stories, past births, lectures, birth places, extensive explanations, unprecedented things, and explanations of meaning.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:3.7"
msgid "“是謂比丘善知法也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who well knows the Dharma.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:4.1"
msgid "“「云何比丘為知義耶？”,"
msgstr "“How does a bhikṣu know the meaning?”,"

msgctxt "ma1:4.2"
msgid "“謂比丘知彼彼說義是彼義、是此義，”,"
msgstr "“It means a bhikṣu knows the meaning of this or that expression is this or that meaning.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:4.3"
msgid "“是謂比丘為知義也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who knows the meaning.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:4.4"
msgid "“若有比丘不知義者，謂不知彼彼說義是彼義、是此義，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who doesn’t know the meaning, which is to say that he doesn’t know the meaning of this or that expression is this or that meaning.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:4.5"
msgid "“如是比丘為不知義。”,"
msgstr "“Such a bhikṣu doesn’t know the meaning.”,"

#. <a class="t" id="421b"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:4.6"
msgid "“若有比丘善知義者，謂知彼彼說義是彼義、是此義，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who well knows the meaning, which is to say that he knows the meaning of this or that expression is this or that meaning.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:4.7"
msgid "“是謂比丘善知義也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who well knows the meaning.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:5.1"
msgid "“「云何比丘為知時耶？”,"
msgstr "“How does a bhikṣu know the time?”,"

msgctxt "ma1:5.2"
msgid "“謂比丘知是時修下相，是時修高相，是時修捨相，”,"
msgstr "“It means a bhikṣu knows the time to cultivate lower qualities, the time to cultivate higher qualities, and the time to cultivate qualities of indifference.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:5.3"
msgid "“是謂比丘為知時也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who knows the time.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:5.4"
msgid "“若有比丘不知時者，謂不知是時修下相，是時修高相，是時修捨相，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there a bhikṣu who doesn’t know the time, which is to say that he doesn’t know the time to cultivate lower qualities, the time to cultivate higher qualities, and the time to cultivate qualities of indifference.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:5.5"
msgid "“如是比丘為不知時。”,"
msgstr "“Such a bhikṣu doesn’t know the time.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:5.6"
msgid "“若有比丘善知時者，謂知是時修下相，是時修高相，是時修捨相，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who well knows the time, which is to say that he knows the time to cultivate lower qualities, the time to cultivate higher qualities, and the time to cultivate qualities of indifference.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:5.7"
msgid "“是謂比丘善知時也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called the bhikṣu who well knows the time.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:6.1"
msgid "“「云何比丘為知節耶？”,"
msgstr "“How does a bhikṣu know moderation?”,"

msgctxt "ma1:6.2"
msgid "“謂比丘知節，若飲若食、若去若住、若坐若臥、若語若默、若大小便，捐除睡眠，修行正智，”,"
msgstr "“It means a bhikṣu knows moderation whether he is drinking, eating, departing, standing, sitting, laying down, speaking, being silent, or relieving himself, rousing himself when drowsy and cultivating right knowledge.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:6.3"
msgid "“是謂比丘為知節也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who knows moderation.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:6.4"
msgid "“若有比丘不知節者，謂不知若飲若食、若去若住、若坐若臥、若語若默、若大小便，捐除睡眠，修行正智，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who doesn’t know moderation, which is to say that he doesn’t know it whether he is drinking, eating, departing, standing, sitting, laying down, speaking, being silent, or relieving himself, rousing himself when drowsy and cultivating right knowledge.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:6.5"
msgid "“如是比丘為不知節。”,"
msgstr "“Such a bhikṣu doesn’t know moderation.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:6.6"
msgid "“若有比丘善知節者，謂知若飲若食，若去若住，若坐若臥、若語若默、若大小便，捐除睡眠，修行正智，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who well knows moderation, which is to say that he well knows it whether he is drinking, eating, departing, standing, sitting, laying down, speaking, being silent, relieving himself, rousing himself when drowsy and cultivating right knowledge.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:6.7"
msgid "“是謂比丘善知節也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who well knows moderation.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:7:1"
msgid "“「云何比丘為知己耶？”,"
msgstr "“How does a bhikṣu know himself?”,"

msgctxt "ma1:7.2"
msgid "“謂比丘自知我有爾所信、戒、聞、施、慧、辯、阿含及所得，”,"
msgstr "“It means a bhikṣu knows ‘Such are my attainments of belief, discipline, learning, generosity, wisdom, discernment, and the Āgamas.’”,"

msgctxt "ma1:7.3"
msgid "“是謂比丘為知己也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who knows himself.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:7.4"
msgid "“若有比丘不知己者，謂不自知我有爾所信、戒、聞、施、慧、辯、阿含及所得，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who doesn’t know himself, which is to say that he doesn’t know ‘Such are my attainments of belief, discipline, learning, generosity, wisdom, discernment, and the Āgamas.’”,"

msgctxt "ma1:7.5"
msgid "“如是比丘為不知己。”,"
msgstr "“Such a bhikṣu doesn’t know himself.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:7.6"
msgid "“若有比丘善知己者，謂自知我有爾所信、戒、聞、施、慧、辯、阿含及所得，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose a bhikṣu well knows himself, which is to say that he knows ‘Such are my attainments of belief, discipline, learning, generosity, wisdom, discernment, and the Āgamas.’”,"

msgctxt "ma1:7.7"
msgid "“是謂比丘善知己也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who well knows himself.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:8.1"
msgid "“「云何比丘為知眾耶？”,"
msgstr "“How does a bhikṣu know the assembly?”,"

msgctxt "ma1:8.2"
msgid "“謂比丘知此剎利眾、此梵志眾、此居士眾、此沙門眾，”,"
msgstr "“It means a bhikṣu knows ‘This is a kṣatriya assembly, this is a brāhmaṇa assembly, this is a householder assembly, and this is a śramaṇa assembly.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:8.3"
msgid "“我於彼眾應如是去、如是住、如是坐、如是語、如是默，”,"
msgstr "“In those assemblies, I should thus depart, thus stand, thus sit, thus speak, and thus be silent.’”,"

msgctxt "ma1:8.4"
msgid "“是謂比丘為知眾也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who knows the assembly.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:8.5"
msgid "“若有比丘不知眾者，謂不知此剎利眾、此梵志眾、此居士眾、此沙門眾，”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who doesn’t know the assembly, which is to say that he doesn’t know ‘This is a kṣatriya assembly, this is a brāhmaṇa assembly, this is a householder assembly, and this is a śramaṇa assembly.”,"

#. <a class="t" id="421c"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:8.6"
msgid "“我於彼眾應如是去、如是住、如是坐、如是語、如是默，”,"
msgstr "“In those assemblies, I should thus go, thus stand, thus sit, thus speak, and thus be silent.’”,"

msgctxt "ma1:8.7"
msgid "“如是比丘為不知眾。”,"
msgstr "“Such a bhikṣu doesn’t know the assembly.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:8.8"
msgid "“若有比丘善知眾者，謂知此剎利眾、此梵志眾、此居士眾、此沙門眾、”,"
msgstr "“Suppose there is a bhikṣu who well knows the assembly, which is to say that he well knows ‘This is a kṣatriya assembly, this is a brāhmaṇa assembly, this is a householder assembly, and this is a śramaṇa assembly.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:8.9"
msgid "“我於彼眾應如是去、如是住、如是坐、如是語、如是默，”,"
msgstr "“In those assemblies, I should thus go, thus stand, thus sit, thus speak, and thus be silent.’”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:8.10"
msgid "“是謂比丘善知眾也。”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who well knows the assembly.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:9.1"
msgid "“「云何比丘知人勝如？”,"
msgstr "“How does a bhikṣu know the greater likenesses of people?”,"

msgctxt "ma1:9.2"
msgid "“謂比丘知有二種人，有信、有不信；”,"
msgstr "“It means a bhikṣu knows there are two kinds of people: believers and non-believers.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:9.3"
msgid "“若信者勝，”,"
msgstr "“If someone is a believer, he is greater;”,"

msgctxt "ma1:9.4"
msgid "“不信者為不如也。”,"
msgstr "“a non-believer is not.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:10.1"
msgid "“謂信人復有二種，”,"
msgstr "“It also means that there are two kinds of faithful people:”,"

msgctxt "ma1:10.2"
msgid "“有數往見比丘、有不數往見比丘；”,"
msgstr "“those who frequently go to see the bhikṣus and those who don’t frequently go to see the bhikṣus.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:10.3"
msgid "“若數往見比丘者勝，”,"
msgstr "“If someone frequently goes to see the bhikṣus, he is greater;”,"

msgctxt "ma1:10.4"
msgid "“不數往見比丘者為不如也。”,"
msgstr "“someone who doesn’t frequently go to see the bhikṣus is not.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:11.1"
msgid "“謂數往見比丘人復有二種，”,"
msgstr "“It also means that there are two kinds of people who frequently go to see the bhikṣus:”,"

msgctxt "ma1:11.2"
msgid "“有禮敬比丘、有不禮敬比丘；”,"
msgstr "“those who revere the bhikṣus and those who don’t revere the bhikṣus.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:11.3"
msgid "“若禮敬比丘者勝，”,"
msgstr "“If someone reveres the bhikṣus, he is greater;”,"

msgctxt "ma1:11.4"
msgid "“不禮敬比丘者為不如也。”,"
msgstr "“someone who doesn’t revere the bhikṣus is not.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:12.1"
msgid "“謂禮敬比丘人復有二種，”,"
msgstr "“It also means that there are two kinds of people who revere the bhikṣus:”,"

msgctxt "ma1:12.2"
msgid "“有問經、有不問經；”,"
msgstr "“those who have questions about the sūtras and those who don’t have questions about the sūtras.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:12.3"
msgid "“若問經者勝，”,"
msgstr "“If someone asks about the sūtras, he is greater;”,"

msgctxt "ma1:12.4"
msgid "“不問經者為不如也。”,"
msgstr "“someone who doesn’t ask about the sūtras is not.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:13.1"
msgid "“謂問經人復有二種，”,"
msgstr "“It also means that there are two kinds of people who ask about the sūtras:”,"

msgctxt "ma1:13.2"
msgid "“有一心聽經、有不一心聽經；”,"
msgstr "“those who single-mindedly listen to the sūtras and those who don’t single-mindedly listen to the sūtras.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:13.3"
msgid "“若一心聽經者勝，”,"
msgstr "“If someone single-mindedly listens to the sūtras, he is greater;”,"

msgctxt "ma1:13.4"
msgid "“不一心聽經者為不如也。”,"
msgstr "“someone who doesn’t single-mindedly listen to the sūtras is not.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:14.1"
msgid "“謂一心聽經人復有二種，”,"
msgstr "“It also means that there are two kinds of people who single-mindedly listen to the sūtras:”,"

msgctxt "ma1:14.2"
msgid "“有聞持法、有聞不持法；”,"
msgstr "“those who hear and retain the Dharma and those who hear but don’t retain the Dharma.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:14.3"
msgid "“若聞持法者勝，”,"
msgstr "“If someone hears and retains the Dharma, he is greater;”,"

msgctxt "ma1:14.4"
msgid "“聞不持法者為不如也。”,"
msgstr "“someone who hears but doesn’t retain the Dharma is not.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:15.1"
msgid "“謂聞持法人復有二種，”,"
msgstr "“It also means that there are two kinds of people who hear and retain the Dharma:”,"

msgctxt "ma1:15.2"
msgid "“有聞法觀義、有聞法不觀義；”,"
msgstr "“those who hear the Dharma and contemplate its meaning and those who hear the Dharma but don’t contemplate its meaning.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:15.3"
msgid "“若聞法觀義者勝，”,"
msgstr "“If someone hears the Dharma and contemplates its meaning, he is greater;”,"

msgctxt "ma1:15.4"
msgid "“聞法不觀義者為不如也。”,"
msgstr "“someone who hears the Dharma but doesn’t contemplate its meaning is not.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:16.1"
msgid "“謂聞法觀義人復有二種，”,"
msgstr "“It also means that there are two kinds of people who hear the Dharma and contemplate its meaning:”,"

msgctxt "ma1:16.2"
msgid "“有知法、知義、向法次法、隨順於法、如法行之；有不知法、不知義、不向法次法、不隨順法、不如法行。”,"
msgstr "“those who know the Dharma, know its meaning, go from one Dharma to the next Dharma, conform to the Dharma, and conduct themselves according to the Dharma and those who don’t know the Dharma, don’t know its meaning, don’t go from one Dharma to the next Dharma, don’t conform to the Dharma, and don’t conduct themselves according to the Dharma.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:16.3"
msgid "“若知法、知義、向法次法、隨順於法、如法行者勝；”,"
msgstr "“If someone knows the Dharma, knows its meaning, goes from one Dharma to the next Dharma, conforms to the Dharma, and conducts himself according to the Dharma, he is greater.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:16.4"
msgid "“不知法、不知義、不向法次法、不隨順法、不如法行者為不如也。”,"
msgstr "“Someone who doesn’t know the Dharma, doesn’t know its meaning, doesn’t go from one Dharma to the next Dharma, doesn’t conform to the Dharma, and doesn’t conduct himself according to the Dharma is not.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:17.1"
msgid "“謂知法、知義、向法次法、隨順於法、如法行人復有二種，若自饒益，亦饒益他，饒益多人，愍傷世間，為天、為人求義及饒益，”,"
msgstr "“It also means that there are two kinds of people who know the Dharma, know its meaning, go from one Dharma to the next Dharma, conform to the Dharma, and conduct themselves according to the Dharma:”,"

#. <a class="t" id="422a"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:17.2"
msgid "“有自饒益，亦饒益他，饒益多人，愍傷世間，為天、為人求義及饒益，求安隱快樂；有不自饒益，亦不饒益他，不饒益多人，不愍傷世間，不為天、不為人求義及饒益，求安隱快樂。”,"
msgstr "“those who benefit themselves, benefit others, benefit many people, pity the world, seek both meaning and benefit for devas and humans, and seek peace and happiness and those who don’t benefit themselves, don’t benefit others, don’t benefit many people, don’t pity the world, don’t seek both meaning and benefit for devas and humans, and don’t seek peace and happiness.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:17.3"
msgid "“求安隱快樂者，此人於彼人中為極第一，為大、為上、為最、為勝、為尊、為妙。”,"
msgstr "“If someone benefits himself, benefits others, benefits many people, pities the world, seeks both meaning and benefit for devas and humans, and seeks peace and happiness, this person is the very best among people. He is great, superior, exceptional, greater, honored, and wondrous.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:18.1"
msgid "“譬如因牛有乳，因乳有酪，因酪有生酥，因生酥有熟酥，因熟酥有酥精，”,"
msgstr "“It’s just as there is milk because of the cow, there is cream because of milk, there is butter because of cream, there is refined butter because of butter, and there is ghee because of refined butter.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:18.2"
msgid "“酥精者，於彼中為極第一，”,"
msgstr "“Ghee is the very best of those things.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:18.3"
msgid "“為大、為上、為最、為勝、為尊、為妙，”,"
msgstr "“It is great, superior, exceptional, greater, honored, and wondrous.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:18.4"
msgid "“如是若人自饒益，亦饒益他，饒益多人，愍傷世間，為天、為人求義及饒益，求安隱快樂。此二人如上所說，如上分別，如上施設，此為第一，為大，為上、為最、為勝、為尊、為妙，”,"
msgstr "“Thus is the person who benefits himself, benefits others, benefits many people, pities the world, seeks both meaning and benefit for devas and humans, and seeks peace and happiness. Of these pairs of people as they’ve been described, as they’ve been discerned, and as they’ve been defined, he is the best, great, superior, exceptional, greater, honored, and wondrous.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:18.5"
msgid "“是謂比丘知人勝如。」”,"
msgstr "“This is called a bhikṣu who knows the greater likenesses of people.”,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "ma1:19.1"
msgid "“佛說如是。”,"
msgstr "“The Buddha spoke thus.”,"

msgctxt "ma1:19.2"
msgid "“彼諸比丘聞佛所說，歡喜奉行。”"
msgstr "“Those bhikṣus who heard what the Buddha had taught rejoiced and handed it down.”"
